  "title": "Forklift Operator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Operate forklifts to perform daily put-away and retrieval of goods, ensuring accuracy and timeliness</li><li>Carry out all operations strictly in accordance with standard operating procedures to ensure safe production</li><li>Perform routine daily inspection, maintenance, and basic servicing of forklifts</li><li>Comply with warehouse safety management policies and related regulations to ensure the safety of the warehouse, equipment, and personnel</li><li>Follow management instructions and complete tasks assigned by supervisors</li></ul><p><strong>Working Hours</strong></p><ul><li><u><strong>Working Arrangement: 6-day work week & rotating shift. May be adjusted based on company development and customer requirements</strong></u></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Secondary school education or above; able to operate high-reach forklifts; valid forklift license required</li><li>Hardworking, able to endure physical work, and aligned with the company’s values</li></ul>",
